<!-- §9 What is a premium baby teether -->
<h2 style="font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">What is a Premium Baby Teether Plush?</h2>
<p style="color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 1rem;">A premium baby teether plush combines two functions into one: a soft, huggable plush toy AND a baby-safe teething ring. Unlike budget teethers (silicone ring only, $8-15) or standard plushes (soft but non-functional, $20-40), a teether plush bridges the gap.</p>
<p style="color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 1rem;">The Douglas Baby Fox Teether Plush is the premium category: Douglas brand heritage, 100% silicone teether ring (refrigerate for soothing cold relief), adorable woodland design, and safety certifications that beat generic alternatives. It's the toy that grows with your baby—teething relief in month 3, cuddle companion at month 12.</p>
<p style="color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">Premium teether plushes appeal to parents who don't want to compromise on safety. You're paying for Douglas reputation, rigorous material standards, and a design that's both functional and beautiful. Think of it as the heirloom-quality teether—something you might pass to a younger sibling.</p>

