      <p style="margin: 0;">Primarily 3-12 months (active teething phase). After teething, it transitions to a cuddle toy and keepsake. Some babies use it longer; others lose interest once teeth fully emerge. The dual-purpose design means it doesn't become obsolete—it's still a beloved plush. Many families keep it as a nursery memento or pass it to younger siblings.</p>
